      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly linked to clinical performance: stiffness governs load sharing with bone graft, yield force defines structural integrity margin, and force at 40 mm represents ultimate load capacity. All three are explicitly required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions."
